co.edu.icesi.nextfruit.modules.model

Class PolygonWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • co.edu.icesi.nextfruit.modules.model.PolygonWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<PolygonWrapper>

    public class PolygonWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<PolygonWrapper>
    This class wraps a list of Point objects that form a polygon. It permits to execute polygon operations over it. PolygonWrapper natural order is calculated using a spatial approach where vertical is evaluated first (top to bottom) and horizontal after (left to right).
    Author:
    cjortegon

      • reduceBoxPoints

        public void reduceBoxPoints()
        Groups closed points to reduce the number of needed points that describe the figure. This operation is made by angles matching. Removes all the edges with angles smaller than 30 degrees.

      • getAverageRGB

        @Deprecated
public double[] getAverageRGB(org.opencv.core.Mat mat)
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the average RGB color using a Mat object. It works correctly only with rectangular figures with edges aligned to X and Y axes. This method is deprecated. Use the PolygonIterator and calculate the average color by yourself.
        Parameters:
        mat - The image to get the colors.
        Returns:
        The average RGB value in double[] format.
